cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on the analysis of human word associations and the correlation between response types and respondent characteristics such as occupation and gender. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) as the authors propose a personalised distributed word association model. Additionally, the incorporation of demographic factors into natural language processing models suggests relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study of verbal associations and respondent characteristics may also relate to cybernetics (cs.CY).
